{
  "text": "Proof. We first show that the exponential map is real analytic. This is known, see for example Prop. 10.5 of [CITATION_1] , but we give the proof for reader's convenience. For V \u2208 T z B 3 , z \u2208 B 3 , we let \u03b3 V (t) be the unique geodesic from z with initial direction V . In local coordinates z i , i = 1, 2, 3, we write \u03b3 V (t) = (z 1 (t), z 2 (t), z 3 (t)) and z i (t) satisfy the geodesic equation",
